Package oogasalad.editor.view

Class InputTabComponentFactoryTest

java.lang.Object
oogasalad.editor.view.InputTabComponentFactoryTest
@ExtendWith(org.testfx.framework.junit5.ApplicationExtension.class) class InputTabComponentFactoryTest extends Object
Test class for InputTabComponentFactory. Uses TestFX for UI interactions and Mockito for mocking controller dependencies. Verifies UI setup, event handler delegation to the refactored controller methods, and UI updates based on listener notifications.

    • selectObject

      private void selectObject(UUID objectId)
      Simulates selecting an object by calling the factory's listener method. Ensures it runs on the FX thread and waits for events. IMPORTANT: Caller must mock getEvents and getAllVariables *before* calling this, as onSelectionChanged triggers refreshes that use these mocks.
      Parameters:
      objectId - The UUID of the object to select, or null to deselect.

    • selectEvent

      private void selectEvent(org.testfx.api.FxRobot robot, String eventId) throws TimeoutException
      Simulates selecting an event from the event list view using the FxRobot. Waits for the event to appear in the list before clicking. Mocks subsequent data fetches for conditions/outcomes. IMPORTANT: Caller must ensure the event list is populated (via selectObject and mocks) and that currentTestObjectId is set correctly *before* calling this.
      Parameters:
      robot - FxRobot for UI interaction.
      eventId - The ID of the event to select.
      Throws:
      TimeoutException - if the event does not appear in time.
